answers.body_markdown:
If you mean that you want rows where the most recent state is `&#39;enter&#39;`, then you can use

    select t.*
    from (select t.*,
                 row_number() over (partition by node_id, alarm_id order by alarm_time desc) as seqnum
          from t
         ) t
    where seqnum = 1 and state = &#39;enter&#39;;

If you are looking for unbalanced rows, you can use `group by`:

    select node_id, alarm_id
    from t
    group by node_id, alarm_id
    having sum( (state = &#39;enter&#39;)::int ) &gt; sum( (state = &#39;exit)::int );

